      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know a support line can talk, but they don't get it. they aren't living in this. it's like i'm just a ghost haunting my own life. i look in the mirror and i don't even recognize the person looking back. it's like half of me died with him and i'm just the leftover part that doesn't have a purpose anymore. i'm just tired of pretending that things will eventually get better. they won't.",
